//Update OpenSSL to 3.0 on Centos 7

Prerequisites

Use sudo when needed
Install perl-IPC-Cmd, perl-Test-Simple and gcc

# sudo yum install perl-IPC-Cmd perl-Test-Simple gcc





Download OpenSSL 3.0

Go to OpenSSLâ€™s download page, /source/index.html. Right-click openssl-3.0.0.tar.gz file and copy link address. Currently the link address is https://www.openssl.org/source/openssl-3.0.0.tar.gz

# cd /usr/src
# wget https://www.openssl.org/source/openssl-3.0.0.tar.gz
# tar -zxf openssl-3.0.0.tar.gz
# rm openssl-3.0.0.tar.gz



Manually compile, make, test and install OpenSSL 3.0

# cd openssl-3.0.0
# ./config
# make 
# make test
# make install




Create symlinks to libssl and libcrypto

# ln -s /usr/local/lib64/libssl.so.3 /usr/lib64/libssl.so.3
# ln -s /usr/local/lib64/libcrypto.so.3 /usr/lib64/libcrypto.so.3


# sudo cp /usr/local/bin/openssl /usr/bin/openssl

Verify the newly installed OpenSSL 3.0.0 

# openssl version




